tropolitan Tuscany. She brings to the fore the tensions—over value, money, beauty, family, care, and belonging—that are reaching a boiling point as the country struggles to deal with the same migration pressures that are triggering backlash all over Europe and North America. Tight Knit tells a fascinating story about the heterogeneity of contemporary capitalism that will interest social scientists, immigration experts, and anyone curious about how globalization is changing the most basic of human conditions—making a living and making a life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aClothing tradexSocial aspectszItaly. 0aClothing trade-Social aspects-Italy. 0aClothing workerszItalyzPratoxSocial conditions. 0aClothing workers-Italy-Prato-Social conditions. 0aForeign workers, ChinesezItalyzPratoxSocial conditions. 0aForeign workers, Chinese-Italy-Prato-Social conditions. 0aGlobalizationxSocial aspectszItaly. 0aGlobalization-Social aspects-Italy. 0aImmigrant familieszItalyzPratoxSocial conditions. 0aImmigrant families-Italy-Prato-Social conditions. 0aImmigrantszItalyxSocial conditions. 0aImmigrants-Italy-Social conditions. 0aItaly-Emigration and immigration-Economic aspects. 0aItaly-Emigration and immigration-Social aspects. 0aPrato (Italy)-Ethnic relations. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aChinese migrants.  aItaly.  aeconomic anthropology.  afamilies.  afast fashion.  aglobalization.  ahealth and well-being.  aimmigration.1 aBressan, Massimo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311068858040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226558103423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226558103/original  a978-3-11-